1 AN ACT relating to grand jury service.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 29A IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 Except as allowed under the Kentucky Rules of Criminal Procedure, a person present
6 during any part of a grand jury proceeding shall not knowingly:
7 (1) Record any testimony or evidence presented during the proceeding; or
8 (2) Disclose or disseminate any information gathered while present during a grand
9 jury proceeding.
10 Section 2. KRS 29A.990 is amended to read as follows:
11 (1) Any employer who violates subsection (1) or (2) of KRS 29A.160 is guilty of a
12 Class B misdemeanor.
13 (2) Any willful violation of KRS 29A.010 to 29A.330 for which a penalty is not
14 otherwise provided by statute shall be punishable as a Class A misdemeanor.
15 (3) Any person who violates Section 1 of this Act shall be guilty of a Class A
16 misdemeanor, unless the person is a public servant as defined in KRS 519.010, in
17 which case it is a Class D felony.
18 Section 3. KRS 500.050 is amended to read as follows:
19 (1) Except as otherwise expressly provided, the prosecution of a felony is not subject to
20 a period of limitation and may be commenced at any time.
21 (2) Except as otherwise expressly provided, the prosecution of an offense other than a
22 felony shall[must] be commenced within one (1) year after it is committed.
23 (3) (a) For a misdemeanor sex offense when the victim is a minor at the time of the
24 offense, the prosecution of the offense shall be commenced within ten (10)
25 years after the victim attains the age of eighteen (18) years.
26 (b) As used in paragraph (a) of this subsection, "misdemeanor sex offense" means
27 a misdemeanor offense in:
